MITA KOLA WANKAN - MY BROTHERS ARE SACRED<br><br>
On these many threads I hear many strong voices...happy voices...angry voices.  I see good things and bad things.  They come to me in powerful words and deep feelings.<br><br>
It is wise for me to remember that a man can tell me what has happened... as he saw it, but he must allow me to make sense of it... as I see it through his words.<br><br>
When warriors wish to learn they must choose their words carefully... and they must be ready to listen carefully.<br>
When they wish to fight... they must choose their brothers, weapons and horses carefully... Words are no longer important... except to spur the battle.<br><br>
There are those who are called fanatics.  They are unable to change their minds and are unwilling to change the topics.<br>
Often, good men of both camps reach for their weapons and throw the good words to the ground.  No one learns anything except who has the best weapons and the fastest horses... and who is willing to die for what he believes in.<br><br>
Frightened enemies are often the most fierce... and most foolish.<br><br>
I am Tatekohomni (Whirlwind/Humming) Wambli (Eagle).  I am the son of Bull Elk... Wild Horse...Cho Cof Per T'Soko of the great Comanche nation.  I am the son of Mathowas'tewin, Good Bear Woman who comes from the camp of Crazy Horse... the Great Lakota... the Ogala Sioux.  I have no fear... I own the Earth.  Was'te Lo - Hecito Yelo
